                "analogy": {
                    "slides": [
                        {
                            "title": "Your Body as Your Home",
                            "text": "Think of your body like a well-built home. To stay strong and comfortable, your home needs three critical systems working together: electricity that powers everything, plumbing that cleans your water, and a solid foundation that supports it all.",
                            "myth": "Many people think diabetes, high blood pressure, and kidney problems are separate diseases. They're actually connected like your home's systems.",
                            "lesson": "Understanding these connections helps you see why your doctor checks multiple things at each visit-we're inspecting all three systems to keep your whole 'home' healthy."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "The Foundation-Your Metabolic Health",
                            "text": "Your foundation is your metabolic health-how your body processes sugar and stores fat. Like a house foundation, when it's stressed (from too much sugar, extra weight, or insulin resistance), small cracks start forming that affect everything above.",
                            "myth": "'I feel fine, so my sugar must be fine'-MYTH. Foundation damage happens silently. High blood sugar often has no symptoms until serious damage occurs.",
                            "lesson": "When we talk about blood sugar, weight, or activity-we're not criticizing you. We're helping you strengthen your foundation before it starts cracking. Small repairs now prevent major reconstruction later."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "The Electrical System-Your Heart & Blood Vessels",
                            "text": "Your heart and blood vessels are like your electrical system-they deliver oxygen and nutrients to every room in your house. High blood pressure is like too much voltage running through old wiring. It works for a while, but the constant strain damages the wires and overworks the circuit breaker (your heart).",
                            "myth": "'Blood pressure medicine is for life, so I won't start'-RECONSIDER. Yes, most people stay on it, but untreated high blood pressure leads to heart attack, stroke, and kidney failure. The medicine protects all three systems.",
                            "lesson": "Blood pressure medicine isn't admitting defeat-it's protecting your wiring. Combined with less salt, more movement, and stress management, you're upgrading your whole electrical system, not just replacing a fuse."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "The Filtration System-Your Kidneys",
                            "text": "Your kidneys are your home's water filtration system-they clean waste from your blood 24/7. High pressure from your electrical system (blood pressure) and sticky deposits from your foundation (high sugar) clog these filters. Unlike a house filter you can replace, kidney filters damaged by pressure and sugar cannot be repaired.",
                            "myth": "'I'll worry about my kidneys when I have symptoms'-TOO LATE. By the time you feel kidney disease (swelling, fatigue, nausea), you've lost 75% of kidney function. We protect them NOW while they're still healthy.",
                            "lesson": "Every blood pressure pill, every point your sugar drops, every pound you lose-these protect your filters from damage. We're not treating three separate problems; we're protecting your kidneys from two directions at once."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "The Cascade Effect",
                            "text": "Here's where it gets serious: when one system fails, it damages the others. A cracked foundation (high sugar) makes your electrical system work harder (raises blood pressure). High pressure damages your filtration system (kidneys). When filters fail, they can't remove excess fluid, which raises pressure even MORE. It's a vicious cycle where each problem makes the others worse.",
                            "myth": "'Why do I need 3-4 different medicines?'-BECAUSE we're attacking the cycle from multiple angles. One medicine alone can't stop a three-system cascade. This is strategic, not excessive.",
                            "lesson": "This is why we're 'aggressive' with treatment early-not to scare you, but because catching it when only one system is struggling is SO much easier than trying to rescue all three after they've been pulling each other down for years."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "Breaking the Cycle-Multi-Pronged Treatment",
                            "text": "The GOOD news: we can break this cycle by fixing multiple systems at the same time. It's like calling a contractor who repairs your foundation, upgrades your electrical, AND replaces your filters in one project. Each repair makes the others work better. This is why treatment involves BOTH lifestyle changes AND medications-we need to address all three systems together.",
                            "myth": "'If I exercise and eat better, I won't need medicine'-MAYBE, but don't stop medicine to find out. For many people, lifestyle + medicine together is what works. We can always reduce medicine later if your numbers improve.",
                            "lesson": "When we recommend medication AND lifestyle changes together, we're not saying one isn't enough-we're saying attacking from both angles gives you the best chance of success. You don't have to choose between pills and lifestyle. You get to use every tool available."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "Small Repairs, Big Impact",
                            "text": "Small leaks sink ships. A tiny foundation crack caught early takes $500 and a weekend to fix. Ignored for 10 years? It can cost $50,000 and risk your whole house collapsing. Your body works the same way. Bringing blood sugar from 200 to 160 or blood pressure from 160/100 to 140/90 might not feel different to you, but to your systems, it's the difference between slow damage and rapid failure.",
                            "myth": "'My numbers are only a little high, not worth treating'-WRONG. 'A1C' maintained over years causes the same damage as 'very high' over months. Time multiplies damage.",
                            "lesson": "Every appointment where we adjust your medicine, every week you walk 30 minutes, every meal with more vegetables-these aren't annoying chores. They're you making $500 repairs instead of waiting for the $50,000 disaster. You are actively saving your future self."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "Your Personal Repair Plan",
                            "text": "You have more power than you think. While you can't change your genetics or your age, you CAN make repairs every single day. Some repairs are free (walking, drinking water instead of soda). Some require medicine (which we'll help you afford). Together, these repairs add up to protect all three systems.",
                            "myth": "'I can't afford medications'-ASK US FOR HELP. Many medications we prescribe are free or nearly free. We have resources specifically for patients without insurance. Don't stop medicine without talking to us first.",
                            "lesson": "You don't need to do everything perfectly. Even 2-3 of these actions together protect your systems significantly. Think of yourself as the general contractor on your body's repair project-we're here to advise and supply the tools, but YOU are in charge of the work. And you're capable of this."
                        },
                        {
                            "title": "Moving Forward Together",
                            "text": "CKM health isn't about being perfect-it's about making your house a little stronger every day. We'll check all three systems regularly, adjust your repair plan as needed, and celebrate every improvement together. You're not just treating diabetes or high blood pressure-you're protecting your whole house so you can live in it comfortably for decades to come.",
                            "myth": "'Everyone in my family has this, I'm doomed'-NO. Genetics loads the gun, but lifestyle pulls the trigger. Even with strong family history, you can delay or prevent these conditions for decades with the right actions.",
                            "lesson": "Every visit, we're your home inspection team. We'll measure the foundation strength (A1C, weight), check the electrical load (blood pressure), and test the filtration quality (kidney function). Small problems get small fixes. Together, we keep your house standing strong. You're ready for this."
                        }
                    ],
                    "ui": {
                        "next": "Next Page",
