                                    "mechanism": "ACE inhibitors help your blood vessels relax and widen, making it easier for your heart to pump blood throughout your body. Think of it like opening a tight faucet\u2014when pipes are less constricted, water (blood) flows more easily.",
                                    "sideEffects": {
                                        "common": [
                                            "Dry cough (10-15% of people - see special note below)",
                                            "Dizziness when standing"
                                        ],
                                        "uncommon": [
                                            "Changes in taste",
                                            "Elevated potassium levels"
                                        ],
                                        "rare": [
