                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "specialNote": {
                                        "title": "About that cough...",
                                        "text": "Between 1 in 10 and 1 in 5 people develop a dry, tickly cough with ACE inhibitors. This is NOT dangerous, but it can be annoying. Important: Don't just stop taking your medication. Call your doctor\u2014there's an excellent alternative (ARBs) that works the same way without the cough."
                                    },
                                    "interactions": {
                                        "drugDrug": [
